value.value: Conversion script for the LDM checkpoints.
Path to the checkpoint to convert.
The YAML config file corresponding to the original architecture.
The number of input channels. If `None` number of input channels will be automatically inferred.
pndm
Type of scheduler to use. Should be one of ['pndm', 'lms', 'ddim', 'euler', 'euler-ancestral', 'dpm']
The pipeline type. One of 'FrozenOpenCLIPEmbedder', 'FrozenCLIPEmbedder', 'PaintByExample'. If `None` pipeline will be automatically inferred.
The image size that the model was trained on. Use 512 for Stable Diffusion v1.X and Stable Siffusion v2 Base. Use 768 for Stable Diffusion v2.
The prediction type that the model was trained on. Use 'epsilon' for Stable Diffusion v1.X and Stable Diffusion v2 Base. Use 'v_prediction' for Stable Diffusion v2.
store_true

Only relevant for checkpoints that have both EMA and non-EMA weights. Whether to extract the EMA weights or not. Defaults to `False`. Add `--extract_ema` to extract the EMA weights. EMA weights usually yield higher quality images for inference. Non-EMA weights are usually better to continue fine-tuning.
store_true
Whether the attention computation should always be upcasted. This is necessary when running stable diffusion 2.1.
store_true
If `--checkpoint_path` is in `safetensors` format, load checkpoint with safetensors instead of PyTorch.
store_true
Whether to store pipeline in safetensors format or not.
Path to the output model.
Device to use (e.g. cpu, cuda:0, cuda:1, etc.)
Set if this is a stable unCLIP model. One of 'txt2img' or 'img2img'.

Set if this is a stable unCLIP txt2img model. Selects which prior to use. If `--stable_unclip` is set to `txt2img`, the karlo prior (https://huggingface.co/kakaobrain/karlo-v1-alpha/tree/main/prior) is selected by default.
Path to the clip stats file. Only required if the stable unclip model's config specifies `model.params.noise_aug_config.params.clip_stats_path`.
store_true
Set flag if this is a controlnet checkpoint.
store_true
Save weights in half precision.
